</script><div class='csg-adwrap' id='sasnr-lesson-wrap'><div class='csg-center-col'><center><h2>Mimicking the behavior of PROC CONTENTS</h2></center><hr><div class="card mb-3 code-card lang-default">  <div class="card-header p-2 d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center accordion-header lang-default" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#lessonDesc" style="cursor:pointer;" role="button" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="lessonDesc">    <h6 class="mb-0">Lesson Description</h6>    <span class="toggle-indicator" data-target="lessonDesc">-</span>  </div>  <div id="lessonDesc" class="collapse show">    <div class="card-body variant-description"><p><img src="data:image/png;base64,"></p>\r\n<ul>
<li>In SAS, <code>PROC CONTENTS</code> is the go-to tool for describing a dataset &mdash; it returns a metadata listing with variable name, position, type, length and dataset-level facts like the number of observations.</li>
<li>We use it to audit newly-received data, compare structure between production and QC, and document expected variables against a spec.</li>
<li>R does not ship with a single function that returns the same shape. Between <code>str()</code>, <code>names()</code>, <code>class()</code>, <code>sapply()</code> and <code>nrow()</code>, the raw material is all there &mdash; but we have to assemble it ourselves when we want a clean, tabular result similar to <code>PROC CONTENTS out=</code>.</li>
<li>In this lesson we write a small helper function that takes a data frame and returns a one-row-per-variable tibble (or data frame) with columns: <code>memname</code>, <code>name</code>, <code>varnum</code>, <code>type</code>, <code>length</code>, <code>nobs</code>.</li>
<li>We build the helper twice &mdash; once in tidyverse and once in base R &mdash; and compare the output against the real <code>PROC CONTENTS</code> result from SAS.</li>
<li>After running, we confirm the R output has one row per variable in the input data frame, with the expected variable names in <code>name</code> and a sensible value in <code>type</code> (character, numeric, etc.).</li>
</ul>    </div>  </div></div><div id="codeAccordion" class="mb-4"><div class="card mb-2 code-card lang-sas">  <div class="card-header p-2 d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center accordion-header lang-sas" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse0" style="cursor:pointer;" role="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse0">    <h6 class="mb-0"><span class="badge badge-primary mr-2">SAS</span> (Base SAS)</h6>    <div class="d-flex align-items-center">      <button type="button" class="btn btn-light btn-sm copy-code-btn mr-2" data-target-code="code-block-collapse0">Copy</button>      <span class="toggle-indicator" data-target="collapse0">+</span>    </div>  </div>  <div id="collapse0" class="collapse">    <div class="card-body">      <div class="variant-code" id="code-block-collapse0"><pre><code class="language-sas-mini">*==============================================================================;
* Step 1: create a small DM-like dataset                                       ;
*==============================================================================;
data dm;
  infile cards truncover dlm=&quot;|&quot;;
  length domain $2 usubjid $5 sex $3;
  input usubjid $ sex $ age;
  domain = &quot;DM&quot;;
  label usubjid = &quot;Unique Subject Identifier&quot;;
  cards;
1001|M|72
1002|F|65
1003|F|45
1004|M|40
1005|F|35
1006|F|6
1007|F|5
;
run;

*==============================================================================;
* Step 2: run PROC CONTENTS and capture the metadata in a dataset              ;
*==============================================================================;
proc contents data = dm out = meta01 noprint;
run;

*------------------------------------------------------------------------------;
* Step 3: print the metadata columns we care about                            ;
*------------------------------------------------------------------------------;
proc print data = meta01 noobs;
  var memname name varnum type length nobs;
run;</code></pre>      </div><div class="variant-description mt-2"><ul>
<li>To get a dataset-level metadata listing in SAS, we run <code>PROC CONTENTS</code> on the target dataset. By default it writes a listing to the output window.</li>
<li>When we want the metadata as a SAS dataset (so we can filter or join it downstream), we add the <code>out=</code> option &mdash; PROC CONTENTS then writes one row per variable to the named output dataset.</li>
<li>We add <code>noprint</code> so PROC CONTENTS does not also dump the listing to the output window when all we want is the <code>meta01</code> dataset.</li>
<li>The key columns in the <code>out=</code> dataset are <code>memname</code> (dataset name), <code>name</code> (variable name), <code>varnum</code> (position), <code>type</code> (1 = numeric, 2 = character), <code>length</code> (storage length in bytes) and <code>nobs</code> (number of observations in the parent dataset).</li>
<li>We then print the subset of columns we care about with <code>PROC PRINT</code>, which gives us a clean tabular view &mdash; exactly the shape we aim to reproduce in R.</li>
<li>One gotcha: the <code>type</code> column in <code>meta01</code> uses 1/2 encoding, not the words &ldquo;numeric&rdquo; and &ldquo;character&rdquo;. In the R versions below we emit readable class names (<code>character</code>, <code>numeric</code>) instead, which is friendlier for a listing.</li>
</ul></div>    </div>  </div></div><div class="card mb-2 code-card lang-r-tidyverse">  <div class="card-header p-2 d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center accordion-header lang-r-tidyverse" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse1" style="cursor:pointer;" role="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse1">    <h6 class="mb-0"><span class="badge badge-success mr-2">R</span> (tidyverse)</h6>    <div class="d-flex align-items-center">      <button type="button" class="btn btn-light btn-sm copy-code-btn mr-2" data-target-code="code-block-collapse1">Copy</button>      <span class="toggle-indicator" data-target="collapse1">+</span>    </div>  </div>  <div id="collapse1" class="collapse">    <div class="card-body">      <div class="variant-code" id="code-block-collapse1"><pre><code class="language-r">library(tidyverse)

#==============================================================================
# Step 1: create the same small DM-like dataset
#==============================================================================
dm &lt;- tribble(
  ~usubjid, ~sex, ~age,
  &quot;1001&quot;,   &quot;M&quot;,  72,
  &quot;1002&quot;,   &quot;F&quot;,  65,
  &quot;1003&quot;,   &quot;F&quot;,  45,
  &quot;1004&quot;,   &quot;M&quot;,  40,
  &quot;1005&quot;,   &quot;F&quot;,  35,
  &quot;1006&quot;,   &quot;F&quot;,   6,
  &quot;1007&quot;,   &quot;F&quot;,   5
) %&gt;%
  mutate(domain = &quot;DM&quot;) %&gt;%
  relocate(domain, .before = usubjid)

#==============================================================================
# Step 2: define a helper that mimics PROC CONTENTS out=
#==============================================================================
proc_contents_out &lt;- function(data) {
  memname &lt;- deparse(substitute(data))

  tibble(
    memname = memname,
    name    = names(data),
    varnum  = seq_along(data),
    type    = data %&gt;% map_chr(~ class(.x)[1]),
    length  = data %&gt;% map_dbl(~ {
      if (is.character(.x)) {
        suppressWarnings(max(nchar(.x), na.rm = TRUE))
      } else if (is.numeric(.x)) {
        8
      } else {
        NA_real_
      }
    }),
    nobs    = nrow(data)
  )
}

#------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Step 3: call the helper and inspect the result
#------------------------------------------------------------------------------
meta_dm &lt;- proc_contents_out(dm)
print(meta_dm)</code></pre>      </div><div class="variant-description mt-2"><ul>
<li>To mimic PROC CONTENTS in tidyverse, we wrap the logic in a small function that takes a data frame and returns a tibble with one row per variable.</li>
<li><code>deparse(substitute(data))</code> captures the name the caller passed in (e.g. <code>dm</code>), so <code>memname</code> in the output matches the SAS convention of the parent dataset name.</li>
<li><code>names(data)</code> and <code>seq_along(data)</code> give us <code>name</code> and <code>varnum</code> &mdash; R counts columns from 1, same as SAS variable position.</li>
<li>For <code>type</code>, we use <code>map_chr(~ class(.x)[1])</code> &mdash; that grabs the first class of each column (<code>character</code>, <code>numeric</code>, <code>integer</code>, <code>Date</code>, etc.). This is friendlier than the SAS 1/2 numeric code.</li>
<li>For <code>length</code>, we emulate the SAS storage-length idea: for character columns we take the max nchar (the shortest storage length that could hold any value), and for numeric columns we use 8 &mdash; the default numeric length in SAS. For other classes we return <code>NA_real_</code>.</li>
<li><code>nrow(data)</code> gives us <code>nobs</code> &mdash; the same observation count PROC CONTENTS reports.</li>
<li>After running, we expect <code>meta_dm</code> to have four rows (domain, usubjid, sex, age) with <code>varnum</code> 1 through 4, <code>type</code> showing <code>character</code> for the first three and <code>numeric</code> for <code>age</code>, and <code>nobs</code> = 7.</li>
<li>The big win over the built-in <code>str()</code> is that the output is a real tibble &mdash; we can filter, join to a spec, export to Excel, or feed into a comparison step.</li>
</ul></div>    </div>  </div></div><div class="card mb-2 code-card lang-r-base">  <div class="card-header p-2 d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center accordion-header lang-r-base" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse2" style="cursor:pointer;" role="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse2">    <h6 class="mb-0"><span class="badge badge-success mr-2">R</span> (base)</h6>    <div class="d-flex align-items-center">      <button type="button" class="btn btn-light btn-sm copy-code-btn mr-2" data-target-code="code-block-collapse2">Copy</button>      <span class="toggle-indicator" data-target="collapse2">+</span>    </div>  </div>  <div id="collapse2" class="collapse">    <div class="card-body">      <div class="variant-code" id="code-block-collapse2"><pre><code class="language-r">#==============================================================================
# Step 1: create the same small DM-like dataset (base R, no tidyverse)
#==============================================================================
dm &lt;- data.frame(
  domain  = &quot;DM&quot;,
  usubjid = c(&quot;1001&quot;, &quot;1002&quot;, &quot;1003&quot;, &quot;1004&quot;, &quot;1005&quot;, &quot;1006&quot;, &quot;1007&quot;),
  sex     = c(&quot;M&quot;,    &quot;F&quot;,    &quot;F&quot;,    &quot;M&quot;,    &quot;F&quot;,    &quot;F&quot;,    &quot;F&quot;),
  age     = c(72,     65,     45,     40,     35,     6,      5),
  stringsAsFactors = FALSE
)

#==============================================================================
# Step 2: define the helper in base R
#==============================================================================
proc_contents_out &lt;- function(data) {
  memname &lt;- deparse(substitute(data))

  types &lt;- vapply(data, function(x) class(x)[1], character(1))

  lengths &lt;- vapply(data, function(x) {
    if (is.character(x)) {
      suppressWarnings(max(nchar(x), na.rm = TRUE))
    } else if (is.numeric(x)) {
      8
    } else {
      NA_real_
    }
  }, numeric(1))

  data.frame(
    memname = memname,
    name    = names(data),
    varnum  = seq_along(data),
    type    = types,
    length  = lengths,
    nobs    = nrow(data),
    stringsAsFactors = FALSE,
    row.names = NULL
  )
}

#------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Step 3: call the helper and inspect the result
#------------------------------------------------------------------------------
meta_dm &lt;- proc_contents_out(dm)
print(meta_dm)</code></pre>      </div><div class="variant-description mt-2"><ul>
<li>For a base R version with zero tidyverse dependencies, we swap <code>map_chr()</code> and <code>map_dbl()</code> for <code>vapply()</code> &mdash; the base R equivalent.</li>
<li><code>vapply()</code> is like <code>sapply()</code> but with an explicit output type (<code>character(1)</code>, <code>numeric(1)</code>). That safety makes it the right tool when we are building a structured output and do not want a silent type surprise.</li>
<li>The rest of the function is the same idea as the tidyverse version: grab class per column, derive a storage-length estimate, assemble into a one-row-per-variable data frame.</li>
<li>We pass <code>stringsAsFactors = FALSE</code> and <code>row.names = NULL</code> so the output is a clean character/numeric data frame without ghost factor levels or numbered row names &mdash; exactly what we would want to export or compare.</li>
<li>We keep the same column order and names as the tidyverse version, so downstream code that consumes the metadata does not care which flavour produced it.</li>
<li>Useful when the production environment is locked down to base R only, or when we want a self-contained utility that can drop into any script without assuming tidyverse is available.</li>
<li>After running, we expect the same four-row output as the tidyverse version: one row per variable, <code>varnum</code> 1 to 4, and <code>nobs</code> = 7.</li>
</ul></div>    </div>  </div></div></div></div></div><script>
    const variants = [{"label":"SAS (Base SAS)","code":"*==============================================================================;\n* Step 1: create a small DM-like dataset                                       ;\n*==============================================================================;\ndata dm;\n  infile cards truncover dlm=\"|\";\n  length domain $2 usubjid $5 sex $3;\n  input usubjid $ sex $ age;\n  domain = \"DM\";\n  label usubjid = \"Unique Subject Identifier\";\n  cards;\n1001|M|72\n1002|F|65\n1003|F|45\n1004|M|40\n1005|F|35\n1006|F|6\n1007|F|5\n;\nrun;\n\n*==============================================================================;\n* Step 2: run PROC CONTENTS and capture the metadata in a dataset              ;\n*==============================================================================;\nproc contents data = dm out = meta01 noprint;\nrun;\n\n*------------------------------------------------------------------------------;\n* Step 3: print the metadata columns we care about                            ;\n*------------------------------------------------------------------------------;\nproc print data = meta01 noobs;\n  var memname name varnum type length nobs;\nrun;","language":"sas","html":"<pre><code class=\"language-sas-mini\">*==============================================================================;\n* Step 1: create a small DM-like dataset                                       ;\n*==============================================================================;\ndata dm;\n  infile cards truncover dlm=&quot;|&quot;;\n  length domain $2 usubjid $5 sex $3;\n  input usubjid $ sex $ age;\n  domain = &quot;DM&quot;;\n  label usubjid = &quot;Unique Subject Identifier&quot;;\n  cards;\n1001|M|72\n1002|F|65\n1003|F|45\n1004|M|40\n1005|F|35\n1006|F|6\n1007|F|5\n;\nrun;\n\n*==============================================================================;\n* Step 2: run PROC CONTENTS and capture the metadata in a dataset              ;\n*==============================================================================;\nproc contents data = dm out = meta01 noprint;\nrun;\n\n*------------------------------------------------------------------------------;\n* Step 3: print the metadata columns we care about                            ;\n*------------------------------------------------------------------------------;\nproc print data = meta01 noobs;\n  var memname name varnum type length nobs;\nrun;<\/code><\/pre>"},{"label":"R (tidyverse)","code":"library(tidyverse)\n\n#==============================================================================\n# Step 1: create the same small DM-like dataset\n#==============================================================================\ndm <- tribble(\n  ~usubjid, ~sex, ~age,\n  \"1001\",   \"M\",  72,\n  \"1002\",   \"F\",  65,\n  \"1003\",   \"F\",  45,\n  \"1004\",   \"M\",  40,\n  \"1005\",   \"F\",  35,\n  \"1006\",   \"F\",   6,\n  \"1007\",   \"F\",   5\n) %>%\n  mutate(domain = \"DM\") %>%\n  relocate(domain, .before = usubjid)\n\n#==============================================================================\n# Step 2: define a helper that mimics PROC CONTENTS out=\n#==============================================================================\nproc_contents_out <- function(data) {\n  memname <- deparse(substitute(data))\n\n  tibble(\n    memname = memname,\n    name    = names(data),\n    varnum  = seq_along(data),\n    type    = data %>% map_chr(~ class(.x)[1]),\n    length  = data %>% map_dbl(~ {\n      if (is.character(.x)) {\n        suppressWarnings(max(nchar(.x), na.rm = TRUE))\n      } else if (is.numeric(.x)) {\n        8\n      } else {\n        NA_real_\n      }\n    }),\n    nobs    = nrow(data)\n  )\n}\n\n#------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Step 3: call the helper and inspect the result\n#------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nmeta_dm <- proc_contents_out(dm)\nprint(meta_dm)","language":"r","html":"<pre><code class=\"language-r\">library(tidyverse)\n\n#==============================================================================\n# Step 1: create the same small DM-like dataset\n#==============================================================================\ndm &lt;- tribble(\n  ~usubjid, ~sex, ~age,\n  &quot;1001&quot;,   &quot;M&quot;,  72,\n  &quot;1002&quot;,   &quot;F&quot;,  65,\n  &quot;1003&quot;,   &quot;F&quot;,  45,\n  &quot;1004&quot;,   &quot;M&quot;,  40,\n  &quot;1005&quot;,   &quot;F&quot;,  35,\n  &quot;1006&quot;,   &quot;F&quot;,   6,\n  &quot;1007&quot;,   &quot;F&quot;,   5\n) %&gt;%\n  mutate(domain = &quot;DM&quot;) %&gt;%\n  relocate(domain, .before = usubjid)\n\n#==============================================================================\n# Step 2: define a helper that mimics PROC CONTENTS out=\n#==============================================================================\nproc_contents_out &lt;- function(data) {\n  memname &lt;- deparse(substitute(data))\n\n  tibble(\n    memname = memname,\n    name    = names(data),\n    varnum  = seq_along(data),\n    type    = data %&gt;% map_chr(~ class(.x)[1]),\n    length  = data %&gt;% map_dbl(~ {\n      if (is.character(.x)) {\n        suppressWarnings(max(nchar(.x), na.rm = TRUE))\n      } else if (is.numeric(.x)) {\n        8\n      } else {\n        NA_real_\n      }\n    }),\n    nobs    = nrow(data)\n  )\n}\n\n#------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Step 3: call the helper and inspect the result\n#------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nmeta_dm &lt;- proc_contents_out(dm)\nprint(meta_dm)<\/code><\/pre>"},{"label":"R (base)","code":"#==============================================================================\n# Step 1: create the same small DM-like dataset (base R, no tidyverse)\n#==============================================================================\ndm <- data.frame(\n  domain  = \"DM\",\n  usubjid = c(\"1001\", \"1002\", \"1003\", \"1004\", \"1005\", \"1006\", \"1007\"),\n  sex     = c(\"M\",    \"F\",    \"F\",    \"M\",    \"F\",    \"F\",    \"F\"),\n  age     = c(72,     65,     45,     40,     35,     6,      5),\n  stringsAsFactors = FALSE\n)\n\n#==============================================================================\n# Step 2: define the helper in base R\n#==============================================================================\nproc_contents_out <- function(data) {\n  memname <- deparse(substitute(data))\n\n  types <- vapply(data, function(x) class(x)[1], character(1))\n\n  lengths <- vapply(data, function(x) {\n    if (is.character(x)) {\n      suppressWarnings(max(nchar(x), na.rm = TRUE))\n    } else if (is.numeric(x)) {\n      8\n    } else {\n      NA_real_\n    }\n  }, numeric(1))\n\n  data.frame(\n    memname = memname,\n    name    = names(data),\n    varnum  = seq_along(data),\n    type    = types,\n    length  = lengths,\n    nobs    = nrow(data),\n    stringsAsFactors = FALSE,\n    row.names = NULL\n  )\n}\n\n#------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Step 3: call the helper and inspect the result\n#------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nmeta_dm <- proc_contents_out(dm)\nprint(meta_dm)","language":"r","html":"<pre><code class=\"language-r\">#==============================================================================\n# Step 1: create the same small DM-like dataset (base R, no tidyverse)\n#==============================================================================\ndm &lt;- data.frame(\n  domain  = &quot;DM&quot;,\n  usubjid = c(&quot;1001&quot;, &quot;1002&quot;, &quot;1003&quot;, &quot;1004&quot;, &quot;1005&quot;, &quot;1006&quot;, &quot;1007&quot;),\n  sex     = c(&quot;M&quot;,    &quot;F&quot;,    &quot;F&quot;,    &quot;M&quot;,    &quot;F&quot;,    &quot;F&quot;,    &quot;F&quot;),\n  age     = c(72,     65,     45,     40,     35,     6,      5),\n  stringsAsFactors = FALSE\n)\n\n#==============================================================================\n# Step 2: define the helper in base R\n#==============================================================================\nproc_contents_out &lt;- function(data) {\n  memname &lt;- deparse(substitute(data))\n\n  types &lt;- vapply(data, function(x) class(x)[1], character(1))\n\n  lengths &lt;- vapply(data, function(x) {\n    if (is.character(x)) {\n      suppressWarnings(max(nchar(x), na.rm = TRUE))\n    } else if (is.numeric(x)) {\n      8\n    } else {\n      NA_real_\n    }\n  }, numeric(1))\n\n  data.frame(\n    memname = memname,\n    name    = names(data),\n    varnum  = seq_along(data),\n    type    = types,\n    length  = lengths,\n    nobs    = nrow(data),\n    stringsAsFactors = FALSE,\n    row.names = NULL\n  )\n}\n\n#------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Step 3: call the helper and inspect the result\n#------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nmeta_dm &lt;- proc_contents_out(dm)\nprint(meta_dm)<\/code><\/pre>"}] || [];

    function populateSelect(selectEl) {
        if (!selectEl) return;
        selectEl.innerHTML = '';
        variants.forEach((v, idx) => {
            const opt = document.createElement('option');
            opt.value = idx;
            opt.textContent = v.label;
            selectEl.appendChild(opt);
        });
        if (selectEl.options.length) {
            selectEl.selectedIndex = 0;
        }
    }

    function renderCode(selectEl, paneEl) {
        if (!selectEl || !paneEl) return;
        const idx = selectEl.value;
        if (idx === undefined || idx === null || variants[idx] === undefined) return;
        const variant = variants[idx];
        const html = variant.html || '';
        const lang = variant.language || 'text';
        const langClass = (lang === 'sas') ? 'sas-mini' : lang;

        // Prefer provided HTML (keeps colors); otherwise wrap plaintext.
        if (html.trim().length) {
            paneEl.innerHTML = html;
        } else {
            paneEl.innerHTML = '<pre><code class="language-' + langClass + '"></code></pre>';
            const codeEl = paneEl.querySelector('code');
            codeEl.textContent = variant.code || '';
        }
        // SAS blocks go through the shared mini-highlighter; others through highlight.js.
        if (window.SasMiniHighlight) {
            window.SasMiniHighlight.applyAll(paneEl);
        }
        if (window.hljs) {
            paneEl.querySelectorAll('pre code:not(.language-sas-mini)').forEach(block => hljs.highlightElement(block));
        }
    }

    function sanitizeCopiedText(text) {
        if (!text) return '';
        return text
            .replace(/[\u00A0\u2000-\u200B\u202F\u205F\u3000\uFEFF]/g, ' ')
            .replace(/[\u200B-\u200D\u2060]/g, '');
    }

    function initCompareModal() {
        const leftSelect = document.getElementById('leftSelect');
        const rightSelect = document.getElementById('rightSelect');
        const leftPane = document.getElementById('leftPane');
        const rightPane = document.getElementById('rightPane');
        const swapBtn = document.getElementById('swapBtn');
        if (!leftSelect || !rightSelect || !leftPane || !rightPane || !swapBtn) return;
        if (!variants.length) return;

        populateSelect(leftSelect);
        populateSelect(rightSelect);

        const tidyverseIdx = variants.findIndex(v => (v.label || '').toLowerCase().includes('r (tidyverse)'));
        const baseIdx = variants.findIndex(v => (v.label || '').toLowerCase().includes('r (base)'));
        const defaultLeft = tidyverseIdx >= 0 ? tidyverseIdx : 0;
        const defaultRight = baseIdx >= 0 ? baseIdx : (variants.length > 1 ? 1 : 0);

        leftSelect.value = defaultLeft;
        rightSelect.value = defaultRight;
        renderCode(leftSelect, leftPane);
        renderCode(rightSelect, rightPane);
        leftSelect.onchange = () => renderCode(leftSelect, leftPane);
        rightSelect.onchange = () => renderCode(rightSelect, rightPane);
        swapBtn.onclick = () => {
            const tmp = leftSelect.value;
            leftSelect.value = rightSelect.value;
            rightSelect.value = tmp;
            renderCode(leftSelect, leftPane);
            renderCode(rightSelect, rightPane);
        };

        // Copy buttons
        document.querySelectorAll('.copy-btn').forEach(btn => {
            btn.onclick = () => {
                const targetId = btn.getAttribute('data-target-pane');
                const pane = document.getElementById(targetId);
                if (!pane) return;
                const text = sanitizeCopiedText(pane.innerText || '');
                if (navigator.clipboard && navigator.clipboard.writeText) {
                    navigator.clipboard.writeText(text);
                } else {
                    const ta = document.createElement('textarea');
                    ta.value = text;
                    document.body.appendChild(ta);
                    ta.select();
                    document.execCommand('copy');
                    document.body.removeChild(ta);
                }
            };
        });
    }

    // Toggle indicators and header click
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
        // Apply the shared SAS mini-highlighter to every language-sas-mini block on the page.
        if (window.SasMiniHighlight) {
            window.SasMiniHighlight.applyAll();
        }

        document.querySelectorAll('.accordion-header').forEach(header => {
            header.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
                if (e.target && e.target.closest('.copy-code-btn')) {
                    return;
                }
                const targetId = this.getAttribute('data-target').replace('#','');
                const el = document.getElementById(targetId);
                if (el) {
                    if (el.classList.contains('show')) {
                        $(el).collapse('hide');
                    } else {
                        $(el).collapse('show');
                    }
                }
            });
        });

        // Copy buttons on lesson display cards
        document.querySelectorAll('.copy-code-btn').forEach(btn => {
            btn.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
                e.preventDefault();
                e.stopPropagation();
                const targetId = btn.getAttribute('data-target-code');
                const block = document.getElementById(targetId);
                if (!block) return;
                const text = sanitizeCopiedText(block.innerText || '');
                if (navigator.clipboard && navigator.clipboard.writeText) {
                    navigator.clipboard.writeText(text);
                } else {
                    const ta = document.createElement('textarea');
                    ta.value = text;
                    document.body.appendChild(ta);
                    ta.select();
                    document.execCommand('copy');
                    document.body.removeChild(ta);
                }
            });
        });

        $('#codeAccordion').on('shown.bs.collapse hidden.bs.collapse', function (e) {
            const targetId = e.target.id;
            const indicator = document.querySelector('.toggle-indicator[data-target="' + targetId + '"]');
            const headerEl = document.querySelector('.accordion-header[data-target="#' + targetId + '"]');
            if (indicator) {
                indicator.textContent = e.type === 'shown' ? '-' : '+';
            }
            if (headerEl) {
                headerEl.setAttribute('aria-expanded', e.type === 'shown' ? 'true' : 'false');
            }
        });

        // Initialize compare modal (admin only; modal exists only then)
        if (document.getElementById('compareModal')) {
            initCompareModal(); // populate immediately
            $('#compareModal').on('shown.bs.modal', function () {
                initCompareModal();
            });
        }

        const toggleAllBtn = document.getElementById('toggleAllBtn');
        if (toggleAllBtn) {
            const panels = document.querySelectorAll('#codeAccordion .collapse');
            panels.forEach(panel => {
                panel.classList.add('show');
            });
            toggleAllBtn.addEventListener('click', function() {
                if (!panels.length) return;
                const state = toggleAllBtn.getAttribute('data-state') || 'show';
                const showAll = state === 'show';
                panels.forEach(panel => {
                    if (showAll) {
                        panel.classList.add('show');
                    } else {
                        panel.classList.remove('show');
                    }
                });
                toggleAllBtn.textContent = showAll ? 'Collapse all' : 'Show all';
                toggleAllBtn.setAttribute('data-state', showAll ? 'collapse' : 'show');
            });
        }
    });
    </script>

